{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d371a61-85a5-4d1b-9888-9dcbccaf7ead","content":"I found **two issues** in the template.json file:\n\n1. **Missing required field `identity`** (line 1 area) — The `identity` field is required by the .NET template engine to uniquely identify the template. It should be a unique string like `\"Test.Template\"`.\n\n2. **Invalid `datatype` value** (line 9) — `\"invalid-type\"` is not a valid parameter datatype. Valid values are: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, and `string`.\n\nAdditionally, as a best practice, the file is missing a `$schema` reference, which enables editor validation:\n```json\n\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n```\n\nWould you like me to fix these issues?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc9f19de-8963-47f8-b7ef-52db95ea5f58","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze this template.json file. This is a .NET template configuration file (used by `dotnet new`). Let me check for issues:\n\n1. **Missing required fields**: The `template.json` schema requires:\n   - `$schema` - not present (recommended but not strictly required)\n   - `author` - ✅ present\n   - `classifications` - ✅ present\n   - `name` - ✅ present\n   - `shortName` - ✅ present\n   - `identity` - missing (required)\n   - `sourceName` - not present (optional)\n   - `tags` - not present (optional)\n\n2. **Invalid datatype**: On line 9, `\"datatype\": \"invalid-type\"` is not valid — the .NET templating engine only accepts `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, or `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `identity` field**: This is required by the schema to uniquely identify the template, and it's one of the core fields needed alongside `author`, `classifications`, `name`, and `shortName`.\n\nSo the main problems to fix are the missing `identity` field and changing that invalid datatype to one of the supported options.","outputTokens":581,"requestId":"33CB:3412D:1F8BCDF:2359010:69E81A04"},"id":"8d797621-